<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-01-0646 </DOCNO><TEXT>The paper reports the findings of Sir Frank Layfield's report on the SizewellInquiry: the Inspector recommended that the PWR station should be built.The recommendation was based on the national need to maintain an economicand continuous supply of electricity, which could be provided by thePWR at Sizewell. Also the inquiry team were confident in the safety ofthe proposed reactor. The Inspector made a number of additional recommendationson topics which included: training of operators, annual dose equivalentfor the Sizewell workforce, safety criteria, radioactive waste management,and generation costs. (U.K.).</TEXT></DOC>